post_text:
HS Athletics may resume tomorrow. All fall sports are considered "in-season" therefore all players and coaches must be cleared through Athletic Office to participate.

JH Athletics fall season has not been canceled, 6 of the 9 participating schools either chose not to participate or to halt until October and make a determination at the September CJHL AD meeting. We are advocating for sports to continue and that parents be given the choice whether to have their child participate or not. Our hope is after the September meeting JH sports can begin practicing with games beginning in October.

There has not been a determination as to whether fans will be permitted at games and if so how that will look. As new information is given it will be passed along.

Apuron Photography
April 14 at 4:25 PM ·

***THIS IS FOR SAN MANUEL*** ***NEW DEADLINE MAY 3, 2020***

***LOW RESOLUTION PICS WILL YIELD A GRAINY FINAL IMAGE***
Try to at least send a 3mb file. We will use what you send but understand that the final image is dependent on what you send us.

***Portrait size only, if its a Landscape portrait it will have to be cropped.***

We have been asked to do Senior Front Yard Banners for the Graduating Seniors.

These will be 2’x3’ banners that can be staked or hung in your front yard.

Cost is $17 each! Apuron Photography will cover the rest of the $25.00 cost

1. You must order from our website, unless you’ve already paid.
2. Send us a high resolution image to - apuronphoto@gmail.com - The lower the quality the lower the sharpness.
3. Please send the file as seniors name. - example - JohnSmith.jpg
4. Deadline is MAY 3, 2020 this gives us time to work them up and gives the printer time to process them.

Thank you and please spread the word, it would be nice to see our town honoring their 2020 Seniors.

Congratulations class of 2020!

Vince, Jeanine and family

Due to AIA cancelling the rest of the Spring Sports Season, the MSMUSD Athletics has decided that:

Seniors who were a member of a team at the time of the initial isolation AND have turned in their uniforms/equipment will receive a refund for their spring sport. (Contact Damon Lovato at the email below for the refund.)

Athletes grades 6-11 that were members of a team at the time of the initial isolation and have turned in uniforms/equipment will receive a credit which will apply to one 2020-2021 school year sports fee.

post_text: UPDATE: PCSO performed a very thorough search of the entire school this evening with the assistance of several other agencies. The report of gunshots has been unfounded, there are no injuries reported nor evidence that a gun was actually fired on the campus. PCSO has cleared the campus and declared it safe for a regular school day tomorrow. Officers will take extra precautions regarding the safety of all students tomorrow while at school to assure our parents, students, and staff it is a safe environment.

post_text: Mammoth-San Manuel USD had a report by employees that they heard gunshots at the school this evening.
